### Transport API Test Requests

### Create a new transport (this will trigger RabbitMQ event)
POST http://localhost:5087/api/transports
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "carrierId": 101,
    "purchaseId": 1001,
    "pickupLocationDetails": "123 Main St, Downtown, City A - Contact: John Doe, Phone: +1-555-0123, Instructions: Ring doorbell",
    "deliveryLocationDetails": "456 Business Ave, Suite 200, Corporate District, City B - Contact: Jane Smith, Phone: +1-555-0456, Instructions: Reception desk",
    "scheduleDate": "2026-01-03T14:30:00Z",
    "status": "Scheduled"
}

### Get all transports  
GET http://localhost:5087/api/transports

### Get specific transport
GET http://localhost:5087/api/transports/1

### Check API Health
GET http://localhost:5087/health

### Update transport
PUT http://localhost:5087/api/transports/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "id": 1,
    "carrierId": 101,
    "purchaseId": 1001,
    "pickupLocationDetails": "Updated: 123 Main St, Downtown, City A - Contact: John Doe, Phone: +1-555-0123",
    "deliveryLocationDetails": "Updated: 456 Business Ave, Corporate District, City B - Contact: Jane Smith, Phone: +1-555-0456",
    "scheduleDate": "2026-01-03T15:00:00Z",
    "status": "InTransit"
}

### Delete transport
DELETE http://localhost:5087/api/transports/1